                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16360160" author="apachespark" created="Sun, 11 Feb 2018 22:57:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;jamesthomp&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/20580&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/20580&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16361990" author="cloud_fan" created="Tue, 13 Feb 2018 08:42:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is an&#160;interoperability problem: although Spark SQL always write out large precision decimal type as fixed-length-byte-array, Parquet spec also allow binary. In Spark 2.3&#160;we may not be able to read parquet files written by other systems because of this bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sameerag&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sameerag&quot;&gt;sameerag&lt;/a&gt; shall we include it in Spark 2.3.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16362730" author="sameerag" created="Tue, 13 Feb 2018 17:45:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, I agree&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
